%N A397728 a(0) = 0, a(1) = 1; for k = 0, 1, ..., append a(k) + p and a(k) + q with 0 < p < q two prime numbers as small as possible so as to avoid duplicates.
%C A397728 A permutation of the nonnegative integers: all terms are distinct; if all the values up to v >= 0 with the same parity as v have appeared, v+2 necessarily appears, at the latest, as the first child of v; as the sequence contains 0 (respectively 1), it contains every even numbers (respectively every odd numbers).
